Key Match Events: Manny Machado threw a ball toward the Dodgers' dugout, which Dodgers manager Dave Roberts called 'disrespectful'.
The game was delayed for 12 minutes due to fans tossing items onto the field.
Jack Flaherty and Manny Machado exchanged profanities after a heated exchange.
Post-Match Reflections: Dodgers manager Dave Roberts expressed frustration over Machado's actions.
Padres outfielder Jurickson Profar faced criticism from fans for his defensive actions.
Padres pitcher Jack Flaherty reflected on his emotional reaction during the game.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was played at Dodger Stadium, marking the first game there after a delay caused by fan interference.
The rowdy fan behavior was noted as a distraction and a challenge for both teams.
